description._content: Description: Sydney Celebrates the Opening of the Harbour Bridge. A fine feature of the evening's festivities was the display of fireworks from Kirribilli Point and Fort Denison. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Sydney Celebrates the Opening of the Harbour Bridge. The bridge under the moonlight effect of the searchlights. The lines of light on the water mark the passage of ferries and speed-boats. The R.M.S. Orford is shown illuminated in the lower ?t-hand corner of the picture. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Sydney Celebrates the Opening of the Harbour Bridge. On the day following the opening thousands of motorists and pedestrians seized the opportunity to make their first crossing. The picture shows the traffic on Sunday afternoon, with cars moving along the newly-named Bradfield Highway on the southern approach to the bridge. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Description: Sydney Celebrates the Opening of the Harbour Bridge. There were over a sc? of floats in the procession, and all were constructed with exquisite taste. Many spectators who has seen similar displays elsewhere declared that they had never witnessed a finer spectac?? either in Europe or America. Location: Sydney, New South Wales, Australia Date: 23 March 1932 ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/607.
